name=Player Model Reload Utility
id=PlayerModelReloadUtil
description=Keeps your character visible through the B42 invisible-character bug without reloading your save. The wall-cutaway hide system (most reliably basement stairwells) drives your render alpha to 0 every frame and holds it, leaving you invisible-but-functional. Auto-Visibility (default ON) re-asserts full alpha every frame so the cutaway can never hold you invisible - hands-free. A manual Reload (keybind default INSERT, or right-click > Utilities > Reload Player Model) also rebuilds model data for the rarer null-mesh glitch. Optional read-only Visibility Diagnostics (off by default) logs alpha state for debugging. Only changes rendering, never the world/grid, so it can't affect your position. Standalone, no dependencies, load order irrelevant. Safe to remove.
modversion=1.2.0
